      "message": "I know you\u0027ve explained this to me before, but I always forget the subtleties there. So idle means that we may call the idle proc while the GrTexture is alive, but just sitting \"idle\" in our cache right? So what triggers us to make this call on these idel GrTextures? Like why couldn\u0027t the cache just drop its ref on an idling GrTexture which I would imagine should trigger a normal release proc?",
